set_algebra.equal

set_algebra.equal(s: SetInput, t: SetInput) → bool[source]

Check if two sets are equal.

Formally:

\[\begin{split}\begin{align*} & \text{Let } S \text{ be a set with elements } (s_1, s_2, \cdots, s_n) & \\ & \text{Let } T \text{ be a set with elements } (t_1, t_2, \cdots, t_m) & \\ & S = T \iff ((|S| = |T|) \land (\forall e \in S, e \in T) \land (\forall e \in T, e \in S)) \end{align*}\end{split}\]
